														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1407530">
									

<blockquote>
<p>&quot;in lieu&quot; should be &quot;in light of&quot; or similar. I am attempting, and failing, to come up with a manner in which someone would be promoted in lieu of recent events.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>True, it <em>probably</em> should be. For those of us who are too lazy too google, 'in lieu of' means 'in place of' or 'instead of'. So &quot;In lieu of recent events, Dr. Bright has been promoted&quot; means &quot;In place of recent events, Dr. Bright has been promoted&quot;.</p>
<p>I have to admit, though, that I'm very amused with trying to come up with an interpretation for that. Maybe the personnel file is telling us that Dr. Bright got his position after some kind of bizarre reality shift? I'm willing to believe it.</p>

