			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1800305">
									

<p>Having read through and thought on all the articles you've written, I think that the articles that are strongest are the ones that somehow elucidate or otherwise use the Foundation through the documentation. Stuff like 963 and 321 are the gold standard that other articles trying to use this type of hook should be held to. But, on the other hand, a lot of your older articles feel like they're holding back on the interesting stuff, and even some of the new stuff has expungement that made me roll my eyes and groan. That seems to be the main issue, the holding back, but your newer stuff definitely does it better than the old material.</p>

